        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(streaming): replace crustacean default progress labels with neutral terms",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nReplaced `DEFAULT_PROGRESS_DRAFT_LABELS` — the built-in pool of automatic\nprogress-draft labels — from crustacean/nautical terms (`Lobstering`,\n`Scuttling`, `Clawing`, etc.) to neutral, technically clear alternatives\nsuch as `Thinking`, `Working`, `Reading`, and `Checking`.\n\nThe old pool was visible to any user who enabled progress mode without\nexplicitly configuring `streaming.progress.label`/`labels`. In technical\nor customer-facing workflows, mascot-branded language in a default status\ndraft is inconsistent with the rest of the system (tool names, progress\ndetail lines) and can make serious work look unserious.\n\nMascot/novelty labels remain available as a documented custom-label\nconfiguration for users who opt in.\n\nFixes #94850\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Default progress draft label pool uses neutral\ntechnical terms instead of crustacean-themed language.\n\n**Real setup tested**:\n- **Runtime**: Vitest unit tests\n\n**Exact steps or command run after fix**:\n\n```bash\npnpm test -- src/channels/streaming.test.ts\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n\n```\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n     Tests  4 passed (4)\n```\n\n**Observed result after the fix**: `DEFAULT_PROGRESS_DRAFT_LABELS` now\ncontains `[\"Thinking\", \"Working\", \"Reading\", \"Checking\", \"Running\",\n\"Searching\", \"Fetching\", \"Processing\", \"Analyzing\", \"Reviewing\",\n\"Building\", \"Testing\", \"Compiling\", \"Resolving\", \"Planning\",\n\"Summarizing\", \"Preparing\", \"Gathering\", \"Investigating\", \"Finalizing\"]`.\n\n**What was not tested**: End-to-end visual verification on Telegram.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- All 4 existing streaming tests pass unchanged\n- No tests reference individual label strings, so no test changes needed\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes` / `No`)\n`Yes` — users with default progress mode settings will see different label\ntext (e.g. \"Thinking\" instead of \"Lobstering\").\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`Yes` / `No`)\n`No` — only the default pool values changed; config schema is untouched.\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`Yes` / `No`)\n`No`\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n- Existing users who relied on the default pool for automated screenshots\n  or label-matching. This is considered negligible.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n- The pool retains the same size (20 items) and same selection mechanism\n  — only the specific label strings changed.\n- Users can restore old labels by configuring `streaming.progress.labels`.\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n- Maintainer review\n",
